event,"Frank: Yeah. French writer. Total loser. Never had a real job. Unrequited love affairs. Gay. Spent 20 years writing a book almost no one reads. But he's also probably the greatest writer since Shakespeare. Anyway, he uh... he gets down to the end of his life, and he looks back and decides that all those years he suffered, Those were the best years of his life, 'cause they made him who he was. All those years he was happy? You know, total waste. Didn't learn a thing. So, if you sleep until you're 18... Ah, think of the suffering you're gonna miss. I mean high school? High school-those are your prime suffering years. You don't get better suffering than that."

event,"I overheard my mom talking on the phone to a close family friend about how I'm going to be moving out in August. !!! Seriously, this whole me-going-away-for-college thing in simply surreal. I'm the first one in my family to not go to OCC. Speaking of OCC... some ho came in and talked about it to our history class, and I was just like ""eff you, woman, I'm not even going there!""... not really though. Aaaand I ordered a Cal Poly jacket tonight. Yesssssssssssssssss."
event,"I'm going to Cal Poly SLO!!

event,"So today, at the Macy's Prom Fashion show (which Matthew starrred in btw) I got my fortune read for free and it was surprisingly accurate. She said that I've faced disappointment, but that I have my own way of getting out of it (true); that I have a bad temper, but get over it in about 5 minutes (true); that I can't stand being bossed around, I like being the boss of myself (SO true); that in the next year and a half I'll be a lot happier than I am now (going off to college?); that I need to focus on school and my career (bring up that D in math?); that I need to work on my confidence; and finally, that she sees 2 kids in my future (weird? maybe a cousin having babies? I don't know). Anyways, I thought it was really interesting, so I thought I'd tell you all about it.
event,"I'm going on my last official visit to San Diego State on Sunday and Monday then I'm going to decide where I'm going to college. Which will it be Cal Poly SLO or San Diego State?"
